trans-unit.source: Contains values passed to the ASP.NET compiler during precompilation.
trans-unit.target: Contiene i valori passati al compilatore di ASP.NET durante la precompilazione.

trans-unit.source: ASP.NET Web pages and code files can be precompiled to facilitate a faster response for users and allow for the deployment of the site without deploying the source code.
trans-unit.target: È possibile precompilare le pagine Web ASP.NET e i file di codice per facilitare i tempi di risposta per gli utenti e consentire la distribuzione del sito senza distribuire il codice sorgente.

trans-unit.source: For more information on precompiling an ASP.NET Web site, see [ASP.NET Web Site Project Precompilation Overview](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Per ulteriori informazioni sulla precompilazione di un sito Web ASP.NET, vedere [Cenni preliminari sulla precompilazione di progetto sito Web ASP.NET](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

trans-unit.source: The ClientBuildManagerParameter class stores values that are used during precompilation.
trans-unit.target: La classe ClientBuildManagerParameter archivia i valori utilizzati durante la precompilazione.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A> property determines how the assembly will be built.
trans-unit.target: Il <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A>proprietà determina come verrà compilato l'assembly.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, you can set <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A> to <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> to recompile any previously compiled components, or set it to <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> to permit the resulting assembly to overwrite any components in the target directory.
trans-unit.target: Ad esempio, è possibile impostare <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A>a <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>per ricompilare tutti i componenti precedentemente compilati o impostarlo su <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>per consentire l'assembly risultante per sovrascrivere eventuali componenti nella directory di destinazione.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> enumerator has a <xref:System.FlagsAttribute> attribute that allows a bitwise combination of its member values.
trans-unit.target: Il <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>enumeratore ha un <xref:System.FlagsAttribute>attributo che consente una combinazione bit per bit dei valori dei membri.</xref:System.FlagsAttribute> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A> property can contain more than one value from the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> enumeration to specify a combination of precompilation behaviors.
trans-unit.target: Il <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A>proprietà può contenere più di un valore di <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>enumerazione per specificare una combinazione di comportamenti di precompilazione.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A>

trans-unit.source: Either the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyContainer%2A> property or the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A> property is assigned a value to create a strong-named assembly.
trans-unit.target: Sia il <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyContainer%2A>proprietà o <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A>proprietà viene assegnato un valore per creare un assembly con nome sicuro.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyContainer%2A>

trans-unit.source: Both values do not need to be set to create a strong-named assembly.
trans-unit.target: Entrambi i valori non è necessario impostare per creare un assembly con nome sicuro.

trans-unit.source: A ClientBuildManagerParameter object is passed to the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManager> object through the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManager.%23ctor%2A> constructor.
trans-unit.target: Un oggetto ClientBuildManagerParameter viene passato per il <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManager>mediante il <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManager.%23ctor%2A>costruttore.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManager.%23ctor%2A> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManager>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Inizializza una nuova istanza di <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter"> </xref> classe.

trans-unit.source: This constructor does not initialize any property values.
trans-unit.target: Questo costruttore non inizializza i valori di proprietà.

trans-unit.source: Those values must be set through the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyContainer%2A>, <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A>, and <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A> properties after the object has been created.
trans-unit.target: Tali valori devono essere impostati tramite il <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyContainer%2A>, <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A>, e <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A>proprietà dopo aver creato l'oggetto.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.PrecompilationFlags%2A> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyContainer%2A>

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets excluded virtual paths.
trans-unit.target: Ottiene o imposta esclusi percorsi virtuali.

trans-unit.source: Excluded virtual paths.
trans-unit.target: Esclusi i percorsi virtuali.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the flags that determine precompilation behavior.
trans-unit.target: Ottiene o imposta i flag che determinano il comportamento di precompilazione.

trans-unit.source: The PrecompilationFlags property determines how the assembly will be built.
trans-unit.target: La proprietà PrecompilationFlags determina come verrà compilato l'assembly.

trans-unit.source: For example, you can set PrecompilationFlags to <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> to recompile any previously compiled components, or set it to <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> to permit the resulting assembly to overwrite any components in the target directory.
trans-unit.target: Ad esempio, è possibile impostare PrecompilationFlags <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>per ricompilare tutti i componenti precedentemente compilati o impostarlo su <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>per consentire l'assembly risultante per sovrascrivere eventuali componenti nella directory di destinazione.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> enumerator has a <xref:System.FlagsAttribute> attribute that allows a bitwise combination of its member values.
trans-unit.target: Il <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>enumeratore ha un <xref:System.FlagsAttribute>attributo che consente una combinazione bit per bit dei valori dei membri.</xref:System.FlagsAttribute> </xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>

trans-unit.source: The PrecompilationFlags property can contain more than one value from the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags> enumeration to specify a combination of precompilation behaviors.
trans-unit.target: La proprietà PrecompilationFlags può contenere più di un valore di <xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>enumerazione per specificare una combinazione di comportamenti di precompilazione.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags"></xref> for a client build.
trans-unit.target: Il <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.PrecompilationFlags"> </xref> per una compilazione di client.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the key container used during compilation.
trans-unit.target: Ottiene o imposta il contenitore di chiavi utilizzato durante la compilazione.

trans-unit.source: Either the StrongNameKeyContainer property or the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A> property is assigned a value to create a strong-named assembly.
trans-unit.target: La proprietà StrongNameKeyContainer o <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A>proprietà viene assegnato un valore per creare un assembly con nome sicuro.</xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyFile%2A>

trans-unit.source: Both values do not need to be set to create a strong-named assembly.
trans-unit.target: Entrambi i valori non è necessario impostare per creare un assembly con nome sicuro.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> of the value for the key container.
trans-unit.target: Oggetto <xref:System.String>del valore per il contenitore di chiavi.</xref:System.String>

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the key file used during compilation.
trans-unit.target: Ottiene o imposta il file di chiave utilizzato durante la compilazione.

trans-unit.source: Either the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.ClientBuildManagerParameter.StrongNameKeyContainer%2A> property or the StrongNameKeyFile property is assigned a value to create a strong-named assembly.

trans-unit.source: Both values do not need to be set to create a strong-named assembly.
trans-unit.target: Entrambi i valori non è necessario impostare per creare un assembly con nome sicuro.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.String> of the value for the key file.
trans-unit.target: Oggetto <xref:System.String>del valore per il file di chiave.</xref:System.String>
